steps to  Install Azure CLI


Download Azure CLI on windows

https://aka.ms/installazurecliwindows

Once you complete the download,  you can Install the .msi file to get started with azure cli

Open CMD
type az --help --> to test whether Azure CLI is installed correctly or not

Once Installation is completed, You can connect to azure start interacting with azure cloud resources

az login
az account set --subscription <SubscriptionName> --> Incase if we have multiple subscriptions
az aks get-credentials --resource-group=<RGNAME> --name=<AKSCLUSTERNAME>

Kubectl is a command line utility to interact with kubernetes cluster.

Download the kubectl ( command line utility)

Install kubectl on your Local Windows Machine

curl -LO https://dl.k8s.io/release/v1.22.0/bin/windows/amd64/kubectl.exe
